@page "/components/ide"
@inherits LocalizedPage

<PageTitle>@GalleryStrings.Ide_Title - Flare</PageTitle>

<GalleryPageTitle Api="FlareIdeLayout">
    <FlareText Typo="TypographyScale.HeadlineMedium">@GalleryStrings.Ide_Title</FlareText>
    <FlareText Color="FlareColor.OnSurfaceVariant" Typo="TypographyScale.BodyLarge">@GalleryStrings.Ide_Subtitle</FlareText>
</GalleryPageTitle>

<FlareStack Gap="FlareSpacing.Medium" Style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
    <FlareText Typo="TypographyScale.BodyMedium">
        <strong>FlareIdeLayout</strong> is the shell of the optional <strong>Flare.Components.IDE</strong>
        package - it arranges the chrome (ribbon, menus, dockable panels, document area, status bar)
        into a desktop-IDE layout, built entirely on the core Flare components and design tokens with no
        custom theming. Each individual part has its own page in the <strong>IDE</strong> group of the
        navigation; this page covers the layout itself.
    </FlareText>

    <FlareStack Gap="FlareSpacing.Small">
        <div><strong>Named slots</strong> - <code>Ribbon</code>, <code>MenuBar</code>,
            <code>LeftToolPanel</code>, <code>ChildContent</code> (the document area),
            <code>RightToolPanel</code>, <code>BottomPanel</code>, and <code>StatusBar</code>.</div>
        <div><strong>Region resizing</strong> - drag the divider between a docked panel and the document
            (or focus it and use the arrow keys); configured via the layout's <code>*Resizable</code> /
            <code>MinPanelSize</code> parameters. For arbitrary layouts use the standalone
            <strong>FlareSplitter</strong> between any two flex siblings.</div>
        <div><strong>Docked panels</strong> - collapsing a docked <code>FlareToolPanel</code> frees its
            space (the region shrinks to a thin rail); <code>Mode="IdePanelMode.AutoHide"</code> makes it
            fly out over the content instead of taking space.</div>
    </FlareStack>

    <FlareText Typo="TypographyScale.BodySmall" Color="FlareColor.OnSurfaceVariant">
        Install: <code>dotnet add package Flare.Components.IDE</code> and reference
        <code>_content/Flare.Components.IDE/css/flare-ide.css</code>.
    </FlareText>
</FlareStack>

<FlareText Typo="TypographyScale.BodySmall" Color="FlareColor.OnSurfaceVariant" Style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    The examples below compose the parts into complete application shells.
</FlareText>

<AutoDemoSection Title="Full IDE Layout" DemoType="typeof(Examples.IdeLayoutDemo)"
    Description="Ribbon, explorer, document tabs, properties, a tabbed Output/Error/Terminal panel, and a status bar composed with FlareIdeLayout. Drag the dividers between regions to resize them (or focus a divider and use the arrow keys); collapse the explorer to a rail and try the auto-hide Properties flyout." />

<AutoDemoSection Title="Office shell (Word / Excel)" DemoType="typeof(Examples.IdeOfficeDemo)"
    Description="Quick-access toolbar, a ribbon with a dropdown gallery and separator, a backstage (File) overlay, a formula bar, an Excel-like grid with cell selection, and a sheet-tab strip. Click File to open the backstage." />

<AutoDemoSection Title="Studio shell (Visual Studio / Access)" DemoType="typeof(Examples.IdeStudioDemo)"
    Description="Menu bar + icon toolbar, a Solution/Navigation tree, document tabs hosting a datasheet, a Properties sheet with editable values, an output panel, and a status bar." />
